---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_AUTHOR, SOCIAL_LINKS } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead title={`About new_text${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Gaurav Agarwal new_textSoftware Engineer, Devices to Cloud." />
</head>
<body>
  <Header />
  <main class="container">
    <article class="about prose">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>
        I'm <strong>{SITE_AUTHOR}</strong> new_texta software engineer working across the full spectrum from embedded firmware to cloud-native systems. Currently building safety-critical avionics software where a segfault isn't a bug, it's a liability.
      </p>
      <p>
        This blog is where I write about things I find interesting: software architecture, emerging technology, aerospace systems, the economics of tech, and occasionally new_textfood.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Work With</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Languages:</strong> C, C++, Python, Go, Rust, Bash</li>
        <li><strong>Embedded:</strong> STM32, TI, Xilinx Zynq, Yocto, FreeRTOS, Zephyr</li>
        <li><strong>Cloud:</strong> AWS, GCP, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform</li>
        <li><strong>Tools:</strong> Vim, Git, CMake, GDB, OpenOCD</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Open Source</h2>
      <p>
        I maintain a few projects that might be useful:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/GauravAgarwalGarg/CourseHub">CourseHub</a> new_textCurated free courses & engineering resources</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/GauravAgarwalGarg/LinuxPostInstallScripts">Linux Scripts</a> new_textPost-install automation for Ubuntu LTS</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/GauravAgarwalGarg/dotvim">dotvim</a> new_textModern IDE-grade Vim configuration</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Connect</h2>
      <p>
        Find me on <a href={SOCIAL_LINKS.github}>GitHub</a>, <a href={SOCIAL_LINKS.linkedin}>LinkedIn</a>, or <a href={SOCIAL_LINKS.twitter}>X</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }
  .about h1 { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .about h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
</style>
